    "descriptionPlain": "Why? Lets see.\n\"Japanese have the lowest rates of obesity & and diseases.\n\nHere is what we can learn from them.\n\n1. The traditional Japanese diet is a whole foods based diet rich in fish, seaweed and plant-based foods. They do not eat processed foods.\n\n2. It consists of small portions of simple, fresh, and seasonal ingredients.\nThe use of chopsticks also reduces large amount of food ingestion.\nPortion control is well followed.\n\n3. Hot green tea or cold barley tea are the beverages of choice, while alcoholic drinks like beer and sake are rare.\nSo no snacking on junk!\n\n4. The traditional Japanese diet is naturally rich in various nutrients, including fiber, calcium, potassium, magnesium, iron, and vitamins A, C, and E & low in salt, sugar and fat.\n\nThus we can certainly start following their dietary guidelines.\n\nThis eating pattern is rich in nutrients and may provide numerous health benefits, including improved weight loss, digestion, longevity, and overall health.\"",
