    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Why must you follow Khyati's Lunch Menu?\n\nHigh-Fiber: Fiber acts as a prebiotic, feeding #weightlossjourney beneficial gut bacteria and promoting a balanced microbiome. This leads to improved digestion, reduced bloating, and overall gut health.\n\nProbiotics: Curd and buttermilk are rich in probiotics. These healthy bacteria help maintain gut flora, improving digestion and supporting a strong immune system.\n\nMoong is a high-fiber, nutrient-dense legume that aids in digestion. Combining it with fresh veggies adds essential vitamins, and minerals, enhancing gut function.\n\n Including buttermilk in your diet increases the intake of probiotics, which can outcompete harmful bacteria and create an optimal environment for nutrient absorption.\n\nTofu is packed with plant-based protein and is low in calories, making it ideal for those managing weight. When added to your salad, it provides satiety, muscle-supporting protein, and keeps cravings at bay.\n\n(gut healing, inflammation, veg protein, probiotics)",
