    "descriptionPlain": "To know more about our online diet program and how we work, contact:\nBarkha – +91 9152419848\n\nCan diabetics really enjoy Diwali sweets guilt-free? YES! \n\nNutritionist Khyati Rupani from Balance Nutrition reveals how you can indulge smartly this festive season, without sending your blood sugar soaring.\n\nHere’s how to make your favorite Indian desserts Diabetes-Friendly:\n\n1️⃣ Rasgulla, Made with paneer, high in protein & lower in sugar. Just squeeze out extra syrup and pair with 4 almonds for better sugar control.\n2️⃣ Shrikhand (Low Sugar) , A probiotic-rich dessert made from hung curd. Go for homemade or low-sugar versions and top with fruits for natural sweetness.\n3️⃣ Apple Fruit Custard,  Add fiber-rich fruits, use stevia instead of sugar, and sprinkle cinnamon to help stabilize blood sugar.",
