    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Good gut health doesn’t come from quick fixes, it starts with simple, healthy habits.\n\nIn our podcast with Meri Saheli, our founder, Nutritionist Khyati Rupani, shared 5 easy foods and habits to improve your gut health naturally:\n\n✔ Drink chaas after lunch every day to help with digestion.\n✔ Start your dinner with a sabzi—like a salad, soup with veggies, or sautéed vegetables.\n✔ Eat probiotics twice a week such as idli, dosa, dhokla, or dahi chawal.\n✔ Begin your mornings with methi & haldi tea to keep your gut healthy.\n✔ Have one amla daily to boost your immunity and balance gut bacteria.\n\nYou don’t need expensive products, small changes in your daily routine can make a big difference.",
