    "id": "1627",
    "title": "The Hidden Truth About PCOS: Are You at Risk?",
    "category": "PCOS",
    "subType": "Podcast",
    "mediaType": "reel",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "PCOS is more common than we realize, yet it often goes unnoticed, especially in younger women. In my latest podcast, I’m talking about how PCOS leads to cysts in the ovaries, hormonal imbalances, and unpredictable cycles. This can result in complications like fibroids and endometriosis, making it harder for women to manage their health.\n\nDid you know 1 in 3 women have PCOS, and in metro cities, it’s 2 out of 3? It’s time to break the silence, raise awareness, and take action. You don’t have to face this alone.",
    "tags": [],
