    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Roti, rice, and dal, once the pillars of Indian nourishment.\nBack then, they were rich in fiber, gave slow-releasing energy, and brought perfect balance to the diet.\n\nToday? With refined grains and shortcuts, roti feels like maida, rice is just starch… and fatigue, weight gain, and lifestyle diseases follow.\n\nIt’s not about avoiding them, it’s about bringing back the way our ancestors enjoyed food: whole grains, natural ingredients, and healing meals.\n\nThe problem isn’t eating more, it’s eating less of what real food used to be.\nLet’s bring back healthy eating habits, because sometimes the old ways of eating are the smartest ones.\n\n(Indian nourishment, fiber, slow-releasing energy, refined grains, maida, starch, fatigue, weight gain, lifestyle diseases, ancestors enjoyed food, whole grains, natural ingredients, healing meals, real food, healthy eating habits, old ways of eating.)",
