    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "To know more about our online diet program and how we work, contact: Barkha \n– +91 9152419848\n\nIndian cooking is often celebrated for its flavours, but here’s the truth shared by our Founder and Chief Nutritionist, Khyati Rupani: it’s not always the masalas that make food healthy.\n\nThe real issue lies in how we prepare it:\n– Over-frying 🍳\n– Overcooking 🥘\n– Excessive use of spices 🌶\n\nThese habits strip vegetables of their natural taste and nutrition.\nInstead:\n\n-The less you cook and spice, the better the nutrition.\n-Minimal tadka = maximum health.\n-A sabzi should taste like the vegetable itself, not just the spice box.\n\nThe takeaway? Balance your spices, cook mindfully, and let your food’s natural goodness shine.\n\nBecause smart nutrition is about preserving health, not masking it.\n\n(Indian cooking myths, healthy cooking habits, simple cooking tips, minimal spice cooking, tadka vs nutrition, sabzi nutrition facts, mindful Indian recipes)",
