    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Unlock real Nutrition For Kids: In this episode of Pod Talk with Ekta, clinical nutritionist Khyati Rupani (Founder, Balance Nutrition) reveals balanced diet advice, healthy tiffin ideas, and proven Indian Diet For Children tips every parent can use. Whether you’re raising a toddler, schoolgoer, or picky eater, discover child nutrition India methods to help your child grow smarter, stronger, and happier without cutting desi foods like buttermilk, millets, and pulses.\n\nWhat You'll Discover:\n• Top 5 Indian superfoods for children’s immunity and focus\n• The truth about milk, jaggery, sugar, and honey for Pediatric Nutrition India\n• How to pack protein-rich, gut health boosting School Lunch India tiffins\n• Smart food swaps to beat Sugar Addiction Kids cravings and junk snacks\n• Easy immunity boosting foods and tips for Picky Eaters Help\n• Managing snacking, obesity, portion control, and building mindful eating habits\n\nKey Topics Covered:\n• Indian Diet For Children: what to include and why\n• Buttermilk Benefits, pulses, millets, and healthy tiffin ideas\n• Toddler food tips and ways to boost Gut Health Kids naturally\n• Reducing sugar intake in kids without tantrums\n• Immunity boosting foods using Indian superfoods\n• Mistakes most parents make & how to avoid them\n\nWith 75,000+ families transformed, Balance Nutrition offers desi nutrition solutions that don’t ban real food. This episode features actionable advice inspired by experts like Rujuta Diwekar and Balance Nutrition’s Khyati Rupani, making raising strong, focused eaters easy for every family.",
