    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Decode Women’s Health, Weight Loss Myths & Emotional Eating with Khyati Rupani!\n\nIn this powerful conversation, Khyati Rupani, India’s leading clinical nutritionist and founder of Balance Nutrition, joins Mohua Chinappa to uncover the truth behind women’s health challenges, sustainable weight loss, and the emotional side of food.\n\nFrom PCOS to gut health and lasting fat loss, this episode is a deep dive into real, relatable wellness. Packed with practical, science-backed insights, it’s designed to help women of all ages take control of their health naturally.\n\nWhat You’ll Learn:\n\nWhy puberty is hitting earlier than ever, and what it reveals about modern lifestyles\n\nHow PCOS and hormonal imbalances silently affect women’s health\n\nThe emotional connection between food, body image, and self-worth\n\nNatural ways to reverse fatty liver, reduce inflammation, and prevent early diabetes\n\nWhy most fad diets fail, and how to build habits for real, lasting weight loss\n\nMenopause myths busted: the truth about traditional Indian “nuskhe” and healing foods\n\nHonest advice for young nutritionists stepping into the wellness space",
