    "id": "1455",
    "title": "How Real Indian Food & Mindset Transform Weight, Hormones & Health!",
    "category": "PCOS",
    "subType": "Podcast",
    "mediaType": "reel",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Can REAL INDIAN FOOD truly fix your WEIGHT, HORMONES, and overall HEALTH, without supplements, crash diets, or giving up your favourite dishes? In this powerful episode, Clinical Nutritionist Khyati Rupani, Founder of Balance Nutrition, breaks down the 3 NON-NEGOTIABLE FOOD RULES that helped her lose 40kg, reverse PCOS, and transform the lives of 75,000+ clients worldwide.\n\nIf you’re tired of low-carb diets, zero-carb myths, protein powder pressure, and supplement marketing, this conversation will completely change how you look at Indian food.\n\nKhyati explains how protein–fibre balance, bright food combinations, and mindful volume eating beat restrictive fad diets—every single time. Learn how to structure a nutrient-rich INDIAN THALI, eat out smart, manage hormonal health, build a sustainable routine, and develop the mindset & identity shift required for long-term transformation.\n\nThis is practical nutrition for real people, real families, and real Indian lifestyles.\n\nWHAT YOU’LL LEARN\nThe 3 Food Rules for Natural, Lasting Weight LossWhy high-protein, high-fibre, structured plates work better than low-carb diets.How to Build a Hormone-Friendly INDIAN THALISmart combinations for fat loss, gut health, and metabolic balance.Why Supplements Don’t Work the Way You ThinkThe truth about B12, Vitamin D, collagen, protein powders & “gut reset” products.Sustainable Eating Without RestrictionThe “JUGAAD METHOD” to enjoy rice, roti, desserts, eating out, and even alcohol—smartly.Real PCOS & Hormonal Weight Loss StrategiesWhy most women struggle, and what actually works with Indian food.Mindset & Identity ShiftsWhy diets fail, how the brain resists “NOs,” and how identity transformation leads to lasting results.",
