    "id": "1262",
    "title": "The 5 Habits That Helped  Me Lose 40 Kg And Never Gain It Back",
    "category": "Diabetes",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "“Losing weight is never easy,\nbut what’s harder is maintaining the lost weight. As a nutritionist, I lost 40 kg when I was 24 years old. It took me 2 years to do so, & I have managed to keep 37kg away for almost 15 years now.\n\nHere’s how I Did it:\n\n1️⃣ Never ate carbs alone; I always pair rice & roti with dal, veggies, or curd. It balances blood sugar, reduces cravings, and prevents fat storage.\n\n2️⃣ Carry a backup snack; Whether it’s travel, meetings, or long workdays, I never leave without fresh fruits, makhana, yogurt, or roasted chana. It saves me from last-minute junk food.\n\n3️⃣ Morning Superfood drink; Coriander seed + fennel seed water with Cinnamon powder is my daily start. It reduces bloating, improves digestion, and keeps inflammation low.\n\n4️⃣ Stay socially connected; Meeting friends and family often lifts my mood, reduces stress, and keeps my emotional health strong.\n\n5️⃣ 10k steps + 10 minutes of silence; Walking keeps my metabolism active, while silence grounds my mind and focus.\n\nThese habits aren’t fancy, but they’re sustainable, and that’s what keeps all clients at BN losing weight & maintaining it for good.\n\nTag a friend who’s ready for simple wins in midlife :)\n\n(Weight loss journey, Maintain lost weight, Sustainable weight loss, Midlife weight loss, Nutritionist tips, Healthy lifestyle habits, Gut health & digestion, Reduce cravings naturally)",
