    "id": "1255",
    "title": "Fruits with HIgh, Moderate and Low sugar content (Carousel)",
    "category": "Diabetes",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "All of us are talking about blood sugar spikes & foods that cause minimal spikes.\n\nAs a nutritionist, I have not been a fan of this concept. We are taught this in college. Refined foods, high starch & high carb foods will cause a spike, but the entirety of the concept is not that.\n\nTo make things simple, here is a list I made to help you all make wise choices.\nWhen you know which fruits are low, moderate, or high in sugar, you can automatically:\n\n✔ Avoid unwanted blood sugar spikes\n✔ Keep your energy steady throughout the day\n✔ Support your overall health without cutting out the sweetness you love\n\nTo understand this in detail, here’s a reference:\n\n✅ Low sugar (5g or less per 100g). Best for everyday snacking and smoothies.\n⬇️ Moderate sugar (6–10g per 100g). Enjoy in balance, perfect for mid-day pick-me-ups.\n⚠️ High sugar (Over 10g per 100g). Delicious but best treated like dessert.\n\nWhether you’re managing your health, watching your carbs, or just curious about nutrition, this guide will help you make informed, guilt-free choices.\n\nSave this post for your next fruit order, and share it with someone who needs to see this today!\n\nWant your personalised diet plan today?\n\n(fruit sugar guide, low sugar fruits, fruits for diabetics, sugar content in fruits, healthy fruit choices, blood sugar management, fruits and glycemic index, nutrition tips for weight loss, best fruits for energy, sugar levels in fruits)",
