    "id": "1228",
    "title": "Chai Vs Chai Busicuit",
    "category": "General",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "There are so many misconceptions going around which often villainise certain foods.\n\nIt is important to make smart choices about the food!\n\n👉Chai vs chai with biscuits- Drinking just a cup of tea a day won’t make you fat, but what we pair with it matters! Biscuits are usually high in sugars and fats. Make sure to pair your Chai with other snacks like nuts or Makhana.\n\n👉Fruits vs fruit juice- No fruit can make you fat when eaten in limit. Talking about fruit juices, they may seem like they’re healthy, but fruits when juiced lose their fiber content and are basically sugar water!\n\n👉Potato vs fried potato- Potato as it is doesn’t make you fat. When it is fried, it adds calories. The way it is cooked matters more!\n\n👉Dryfruits vs pastry- Yes, dry fruits are high in calories and natural sugars, but if you avoid it for this reason and later land up binging on cakes and pastries, it negates the whole purpose. Eat whole and natural foods over processed ones.\n\nDon’t buy into myths and don’t villainise certain foods over others. Instead focus on what Nutrition you can get out of a certain food!",
