    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Fibre - Blessing or Curse?\n\nMost of us dietitians swear by fibre & its benefits in weight loss, diabetes, thyroid management & many other health conditions. \n\nHence, most weight loss diet is high on fibre & contain foods like brown rice, millets, fruits & vegetables.\n\nA human body requires 25 - 30g fibre in a day.\n\nBenefits of fibre:\n👉 Lowers your cholesterol level \n👉 Helps control blood sugar levels\n👉 Aids in achieving a healthy weight\n\nBut given our current lifestyle, we barely manage to get in 15 g of fibre leading to a lot of weight gain & digestive issues.\n\nSometimes however some diet plans contain a lot more than 40 g of fibre & if had over a long time it can be harmful.\n\nHence, if your symptoms are persistent for more than three months, make sure you inform your dietitian about this & she will alter the amount of fibre for you.\n\nP.S - Make sure you have a good water intake when on a high fibre diet 💦\n\nTo get a personalised plan, comment \"I want a diet\" or DM us.",
