    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Is your high-protein breakfast also a high-fat one? Check here!\n\nThis breakfast plate is not ideal for anyone who wants to lose weight.\n\nHere are some examples of where the most common diet mistakes happen:\n\nMISTAKE:\n- Most of us think that nuts are extremely healthy and must be had in good amounts on a daily basis.\n\nTRUTH:\n- Nuts are high in calories & also fat.\n- A single serving of nuts therefore must not be more than 2 to 3 pieces at a time.\n\nMISTAKE:\n\n- Though eggs are considered very healthy, they are also high in cholesterol as well as fat.\nIf you are looking to lose weight, adding yolks to the diet may lead to no loss in your overall weight.\n\nTRUTH:\n- An ideal weight loss portion for eggs would be three whites and half a yolk.\n\nCONCLUSION:\n\n- Eating nuts in the “right quantity” can help curb sugar cravings & provide you with energy & fat-soluble vitamins.\n- ⁠Having healthy foods is good. However, understand the implication of the overall calories coming from those and portion your meals accordingly.\n\nTo know more about our personalized diet programs,\n\nCall/WhatsApp:\nNutritionist Chelsi: 9820455544\nNutritionist Akansha: 9820792855",
