    "descriptionPlain": "Glowing skin after 40? \n\nAfter turning 40, I started facing dryness, a small freckle or skin getting dull, I decided to research and here is what I added to my daily routine.\n\n5 Indian foods to add for glowing skin after the age of 40:\n\n1. **Amla (Indian Gooseberry)**: Packed with Vitamin C, it boosts collagen production for radiant skin. 🍈 (1 whole, ~30 calories)\n\n2. **Almonds**: Rich in Vitamin E, these help fight skin aging & keep your skin supple. 🌰 (7-8 almonds, ~80 calories)\n\n3. **Turmeric**: Anti-inflammatory properties of turmeric brighten your skin and reduce wrinkles. 🌿 \n(1/2 tsp, ~10 calories)\n\n4. **Sesame Seeds**: High in zinc, they promote healthy skin regeneration and elasticity. 🌱 (1 tbsp, ~52 calories)\n\n5. **Spinach**: Loaded with antioxidants and Vitamin A, it helps repair and rejuvenate your skin. 🥗 \n(1 cup cooked, ~41 calories)\n\n(Healthy skin, skincare, after 40, superfoods)  Will you add these superfoods to your diet?",
