    "title": "4 Reasons why should not add curry leaves to your diet!!",
    "category": "Diabetes",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "If you don’t want to see these changes in your health, exclude curry leaves from your diet!!\n\n1. Curry leaves can be beneficial for your skin, hair, and overall health because it contains phenolic antioxidants \n\n2. They are Rich in vitamin A, vitamin B, vitamin C, vitamin B2, calcium, iron, potassium, and magnesium.\n\n3. Chewing or eating curry leaves regularly helps in the burning of calories & avoiding fat accumulation.\n\n4. Curry leaves contain Mahanimbine and koenigine, which are potent antioxidants. These compounds have anti-obesity, anti-diabetic, and lipid-lowering effects.\n\nCurry leaves are used in almost every Indian household for garnishing but we often remove it from the dishes without being fully aware of their health benefits! \n\nP.S.: To all those who are confused, Curry leaves are actually healthy! Just wanted you all to read the caption : )",
