    "descriptionPlain": "Your Child Doesn’t Need Overcomplicated Food! \n\nAs a parent, you don’t need imported superfoods to raise healthy kids.\n@nutritionist_khyatirupani from @balancenutrition.in shares everyday, desi staples that support your child’s growth, gut, and brain.\n\n- Buttermilk – hydration + probiotics + protein\n- Local green veggies – think drumsticks, cabbage, not kale\n- Fresh fruit – mango, watermelon, targola (no milkshakes!)\n- Millets – try ragi paratha or jowar roti\n- Pulses & dals – the OG plant-based protein\n\nSkip the sugar-filled snacks and start with these simple, locally sourced foods.\n\nComment “KID FOOD” to get the full podcast link in your DMs!\n\nDon’t forget to follow @podtalkwithekta @ektakhosla23 for more such insightful podcasts.\n\nWith 75,000+ transformations, @balancenutrition.in helps real people get results without restrictive diets or giving up desi foods.\n\nDM @nutritionist_khyatirupani for expert guidance today!\n\nWatch the full episode now on the @podtalkwithekta YouTube Channel!\n\n(Wellness, Child Nutrition, Food for Kids, Healthy Food, Nutritionist, Khyati Rupani, Ekta Khosla)",
