    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Losing weight or improving your health doesn’t mean cutting out everything you enjoy.\n\nAs someone who has lost 40kg and reversed PCOS naturally, our founder, Clinical Nutritionist Khyati Rupani, knows firsthand how impractical it can be to give up sweets entirely.\n\nAt Balance Nutrition, we use the 2-Bite Rule — a mindful and scientific way to manage cravings for desserts or calorie-dense treats without derailing your progress.\n\nTwo mindful bites are often all it takes to curb the craving. No need to rely on extremes or eliminate your favourite foods — we focus on balance, not restriction.\n\nThis is how we help clients achieve consistent results in our weight loss, hormonal balance, and gut health programs.\n\nPro Tip: The rule works best when used in moderation. A few thoughtful bites each month can satisfy the mind — and keep the body on track.\n\n(weight loss India, PCOS weight loss, Indian weight loss program, healthy Indian eating habits, mindful eating, real weight loss journey, fat loss without gym, sugar cravings, craving management, sustainable fat loss, emotional eating, hormonal weight gain, gut healing foods, balanced Indian diet, clinical diet plan, sugar craving fix, no fad diets)",
