    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Are Kids Really Picky Eaters — Or Are We Raising Them That Way?\n\n@nutritionist_khyatirupani believes that most kids aren’t born picky — they learn food habits from us.\n\nIf a parent avoids vegetables or says “I don’t like this,” kids quickly follow.\nAnd if kids get exposed to sugar, fast food, and packaged snacks early on, their taste buds get used to junk — making dal, roti, sabzi feel “boring.”\n\nThe good news? You can shape their food preferences early.\n✅ Mix vegetables into parathas or idlis\n✅ Add spinach or beetroot to dal or soup\n✅ Plate food with colour and creativity\n\nYou don’t need imported snacks or nutrition powders.\nJust smart Indian food, everyday habits, and a little patience.\n\n📩 Comment “KID FOOD” to get the full podcast link in your DMs!\n\nFor more such practical parenting and food tips, follow @podtalkwithekta @ektakhosla23\n\nWith 75,000+ transformations across 94 countries, @balancenutrition.in shows real families how to build healthy habits without cutting out Indian food.\n\nDM @nutritionist_khyatirupani for expert nutrition guidance for your child today.\n\n🎥 Watch the full episode on @podtalkwithekta YouTube now!",
