    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Karan Johar claims that what helped him lose weight was not Ozempic but OMAD!\n\n What is OMAD?\n\nOMAD stands for One Meal A Day. You fast for 23 hours and eat just one meal in a one-hour window.\n\nDoes it help with weight loss?\n Yes, but only if you eat fewer calories overall.\n Your insulin drops during fasting, pushing the body to burn fat.\n It can backfire if your one meal is ultra-processed or super high-calorie. \n\nCan Karan Johar’s transformation be just OMAD?\n\nUNLIKELY \n\nThat level of fat loss + facial change + speed point to:\nOzempic or GLP-1s\nFat Loss Supplements\nStructured workouts\nMedical supervision\nOMAD may have helped, but it was likely the whole story.\n\nShould you consider OMAD to lose weight?\n\nFor most people, not really.\nSide Effects Include - Hunger, mood swings, energy crashes & depression. \nWomen, especially due to hormones, struggle more to sustain this diet. \n\nWas it Ozempic or OMAD\n\n(Karan Johar, Bollywood, Ozempic Debate, Weight Loss, wellness Tips, Healthy Lifestyle)",
