    "descriptionPlain": "What did I really eat in Japan as a nutritionist?\n\nI found these light, gluten-free noodles late at night for my midnight cravings from @seven_eleven_japan —zero oil, high fiber, super satisfying!\n\n@donki_jp_en @uniqlo_jp \n\n1. 🟤 Soy Sauce instead of other high-calorie dips \n✅ Adds flavour without fat or extra calories\n✅ Supports digestion\n\n2. 🟢 Seaweed instead of fried noodles or chips\n✅ Rich in iodine (great for thyroid!)\n✅ High in fiber, low in calories\n\n3. 🟠 Pickled Veggies instead of sweets or crisps!\n✅ Packed with gut-friendly probiotics\n✅ Crunchy, tangy & crave-satisfying\n\nThis bowl was light but kept me full, balanced my blood sugar, and didn’t mess with my sleep.\n\nWill you try this combo next time you’re in Japan? 😍",
