    "descriptionPlain": "If you are under the impression that going vegan is about eating tofu, cashew cheese, or almond milk, then you are mistaken.\n\nBy definition, a vegan diet is best explained this way.\n\nThis diet comprises of foods that are plant-based. It means, that, you cannot have anything coming directly or indirectly from animals.\n\nThis means,\nAlcohol is vegan 🍷\nPotato chips fried in plant oil are vegan 🥔\nFrench fries, most breads and biscuits also are vegan 😵\n\nIf you ask me about Indian vegan diets, we have been eating vegan food more than anybody else.\n\nDal rice\nRoti sabzi\nRajma rice\nIdli sambar\nChole\nDhokla\nChillas\n\nThese are all VEGAN too :)\n\nIf you want us to do a video on whether this diet is healthy or not, comment VEGAN DIET and I shall do a live series on this :)\n\nCall/WhatsApp:\nNutritionist Chelsi: 9820455544\nNutritionist Akansha: 9820792855",
