    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "All about the Volume of Foods & Calories\n\nDid you know that weight loss is not just about the number of calories you consume in a day?\n\nYes,\n\nIf you want to lose weight & sustain your diet for the long term, then you have to focus on the foods that are HIGH in Volume & Low in Calories.\n\n✅ Foods that are high Volume & Low Calories: \n\n1. Watermelon (250g): 75 calories\n2. Berries (1 cup): 80 calories \n3. 1 bowl Clear Veg Soup: 50 calories \n4. 1 bowl Kurmura: 56 calories \n5. 1 bowl Saute cabbage: 65 calories \n6. 1 glass buttermilk: 103 calories \n\nThese kinds of foods are very helpful when added to your main meals or snacks as they keep you FULL making it easy to lose weight. \n\n🛑 Foods that are Low Volume High Calories: \n\n1. Coconut Chutney (2 tbsp): 105 calories\n2. Flax/Pumpkin seeds: 80 calories \n3. Paneer (100g): 265 calories \n4. Nuts (100g): 650 calories \n5. Dried Anjeer: 350 calories \n\nThese foods can be called healthy but are not apt for weight loss as they are low in volume & have very many calories.\nYou will end up feeling hungry & not see any loss on the scale.\n\nP.S. Have you signed up for the 1-Day Belly Fat Challenge? \n\nREGISTRATIONS END TOMORROW!\n\nClick on the link in the bio to register!\n\nCall/ WhatsApp:\nNutritionist Siddhi: +91 7304802964\nNutritionist Akansha: +91 9820792855",
