    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "While losing 40 kg, I realized it was never about weighing your food, counting your calories, managing your meals on time, or eliminating foods.\n\nWhat helped me the most to get rid of body fat & belly fat was realizing a big mistake I made with my food. \n\nIt is backed by a lot of scientific research, and there is also evidence that you can lose weight with these changes in your daily diet.\n\nTHE MISTAKE:\n\n‘I was adding paneer to my diet daily & paneer tikka was my go-to at every restaurant’!\n\nNow you will think paneer is high in protein & most recommended as a weight loss food.. here are some facts:\n\n1. 100g raw paneer contains: 25g fat & 300 calories \n2. 1 portion paneer tikka: 900 calories \n3. 1 portion paneer bhurji: 450 calories \n\nMost paneer used in restaurant dishes is full fat; the ones available in the market are also high-fat.\n\nIf your goal is to lose weight, then the addition of healthy foods that are high in calories or fat needs to be kept in check. A low-calorie & a low-fat diet with adequate fiber, protein & healthy carbs will help you get here faster.\n\nI added these low calorie vegetarian protein sources to my diet instead and lost weight faster.\n\nSwap for Low-Calorie, High-Protein Alternatives:\n\nTofu: 76 kcal (100g, 8g protein)\nEdamame: 121 kcal (100g, 11g protein)\nLentils: 116 kcal (100g, 9g protein)\nDon’t let your diet be derailed by hidden calories!",
