    "id": "746",
    "title": "Sweets or fried food craving",
    "category": "PCOS",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "While losing 40 kg, I realized it was never about weighing your food, counting your calories or feeling intense cravings.\n\nWhat helped me the most to get rid of body fat & belly fat was realizing a big mistake I made with my food Cravings. \n\nTHE MISTAKE:\n\n‘I would control my cravings for a very long time, and there would come a point where I would just give in. There are days where I have eaten and entire tub of ice cream or a big piece of cake. I have also done the same mistake with craving of pizza And Samosa.\n\nHOW TO MANAGE CRAVING? \n\nWhen ever I now have a grieving for food that is high in calories and not healthy. This is what I and the clients at Balance Nutrition do. \n\n1. Take two bite-size portions of the food you are craving.\n2. ⁠ Filll a glass of water & keep it beside you.\n3. ⁠ Eat the first bite.\n4. ⁠ Have the glass of water that is around you.\n5. ⁠ Wait for a minute and have the second bite.\n\nYou will be surprised that you’re craving is satisfied, and this also tricks your body into feeling full after eating your craving.\n\nP.S. follow this tip for anyone food per week only.\n\n(Cravings, hunger, 2 bite rule, weight loss)",
