    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "The truth about Healthy Food!\n\nMost of us will always go for foods that are labeled - Low-Fat, Vegan & Most favorite Sugar-Free.\nMost of these fancy labels do not specify the absolute truth. The amount of calories in these healthy foods at times is higher than in regular foods. \n1. Some smoothies can be a lot higher in calories than coke. \n2. Some sugar-free sweets can be extremely high in fat. \n3. A lot of gluten-free biscuits & bread have double the calories than regular bread. \n\nWe see a lot of clients before starting their program with us very troubled & telling us that they are eating very healthy but still not losing weight. \nThis is the main reason. Since it comes with the label ‘Healthy’, the portions sixes are also not kept in control. \nThis leads to gain in weight rather than loss. \n\nIf we compare the image above, you can easily see how a healthy smoothie, a salad & a parfait are higher in calories than regular junk. \n\nTo lose weight, it is necessary to understand these labels & also compare the calories with it’s original counterparts. \n\nNext time you see a sugar free ladoo, be careful to not miss the ghee, the nuts & high calorie dried fruits like dates & Anjeer ;)",
