    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Lose weight with Rice in your diet :)\n\nTime & again, rice has been villainized to be the culprit when it comes to weight gain.\n\nRice is not at all an issue. A serving of boiled rice contains 100 calories. \nSo does wheat, ragi & other millets. \n\nWhat’s the difference? It is the fiber content & therefore the GI (glycemic index)\n\nWhite polished rice is low in fiber, and high in starch & will therefore have a high GI making it unhealthy for overweight individuals & diabetics. \n\nHow to ensure you are eating Rice the right way?\n\n1. Use Brown Rice \n2. Use Unpolished Rice\n3. Use Basmati Rice & eat after 12 to 20 hours of refrigeration. \n4. add 50% veggies & 20% protein to 1 bowl, the rest 30% can be rice.\n\nDon’t forget to like & share this video, not just save ;)",
