    "descriptionPlain": "Nutritionally, granola is healthy & promoted as a go-to healthy snack as well. But is it worth the calories?\n\nThe word calories can be extremely misleading. Also, certain foods have been understood poorly by a lot of us. \n\nA serving of granola (100g) can contain 500 calories & 80g simple carbs! \n\nHere if the calories will not mentioned, most of us would have picked granola as a healthy option.\n\nGranola contains honey which is high in sugar, nuts which are high in calories and fat.\n\nOverall, this is all about portions. \nIf you are planning to lose weight, this may be a poor choice for you. \n\nDon’t forget to like and share this video, not just save ;)",
