    "descriptionPlain": "Makhana Mania & Weight loss!\nMakhana or lotus seeds are one of the healthiest snack from the Indian subcontinent. \nA serving of Makhana gives you only hundred calories, but the amount of protein if compared to popcorn is double :) \nIn fact, you will also find a good amount of calcium and phosphorus in Makhana. \nThe trouble begins when a healthy snack or a food item is packaged and flavored.\nA complete healthy snack turns into a bomb of calories with added preservatives, which are harmful. \nAs a buyer and consumer, always compare the Nutrition labels of Foods. \nThe easiest way to is to compare a healthy food label with an healthy one.\n\nWays to include Makhanas in your Diet without the Calories:\n\n1. Dry roast them in an iron skillet & add salt.\n2. ⁠Make a kheer with skim milk & apple purée \n3. ⁠Make a Raita \n4. ⁠Make a Dip \n5. ⁠Make a Bhel",
