    "id": "725",
    "title": "Tip 7 of SLIM SMART with BN",
    "category": "General",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "“Roasted Snacks is a huge business in the world of weight loss. As a nutritionist, for me there is no gimmick bigger than this when it comes to actual results \n\nHere is why :) \n\n1. Calorie Content:\n\n • Roasted Chips: Although seemingly healthier, a large serving can still pack in a lot of calories.\n • Fried Chips: Higher in calories per gram compared to roasted, but in moderation, they can be part of a balanced diet.\n\n 2. Fat Content:\n\n • Roasted Chips: Often contain added oils and fats to achieve that crispy texture.\n • Fried Chips: Typically higher in fat, but enjoying them occasionally in small portions is less harmful than overeating roasted chips.\n\n 3. Portion Control:\n\n • It’s easier to overeat roasted chips due to the perception that they are healthier, leading to higher calorie and fat intake.\n\n 4. Moderation is Key:\n\n • Enjoying fried chips in small amounts can be better for your diet than consuming large portions of roasted chips, which can still be calorie-dense.\n\nSo, follow the 2-bite rule or Focus on portion sizes and balance in your diet. \n\nIt’s not just about the type of food but how much and how often you consume it. \n\nStay healthy and mindful, everyone! 🌟 \n\n(2 bite rule) (roasted snacks) (portion control) (weight loss) (nutritionist)",
    "tags": [
      "balancenutrition",
      "NutritionTips",
      "HealthyEating",
      "BalancedDiet",
      "MindfulEating",
      "nutrifit"
    ],
