    "descriptionPlain": "When it comes to choosing the right snack, it’s crucial to make informed decisions! Let’s compare roasted chana and roasted peanuts:\n\n🥜 Calories & Fat:\n\n\t•\tRoasted Chana: 120 calories, 2g fat (per 28g serving)\n\t•\tRoasted Peanuts: 160 calories, 14g fat (per 28g serving)\n\n🌟 Why Choose Roasted Chana? 🌟\n\n\t1.\tLower Calorie Count: Perfect for weight management.\n\t2.\tLess Fat: Better for heart health and overall fat intake.\n\t3.\tHigher Fiber: Keeps you fuller for longer and aids digestion.\n\t4.\tRich in Vitamins and Minerals: Excellent source of iron, folate, and magnesium.\n\t5.\tDiabetic-Friendly: Helps regulate blood sugar levels.\n\n💪 Protein Content:\n\n\t•\tRoasted Chana: 6g protein (per 28g serving)\n\t•\tRoasted Peanuts: 7g protein (per 28g serving)\n (Low fat snacks, sattu, weight loss, body building)",
