    "id": "716",
    "title": "High Fiber Diets",
    "category": "Gut Health",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "BEST WAY TO LOSE WEIGHT I FOLLOW AS A NUTRITIONIST: A HIGH-FIBRE & LOW FAT DIET. \n\nMost weight loss diets at Balance Nutrition are high on fiber as that is the best way to keep our clients full & cleanse the gut. \n\nHowever, it can sometimes cause a few unwanted side effects like gas, bloating, & stomach discomfort. Here’s why:\n\n1️⃣ Fermentation in the Gut: High-fiber foods are fermented by gut bacteria, leading to gas production.\n2️⃣ Sudden Increase: Adding too much fiber too quickly can overwhelm your digestive system.\n3️⃣ Slower Digestion: Fiber slows digestion, which can lead to a feeling of fullness and bloating.\n\n🍃 How to Add Fibre & Avoid these Symptoms:\n\n 1️⃣ Increase Gradually: Add fiber-rich foods slowly to your diet, giving your body time to adjust.\n2️⃣ Check Water Intake: Drink plenty of water to help fiber move smoothly through your digestive system.\n3️⃣ Move More: Gentle exercise like walking can reduce bloating and help ease digestion.",
