    "descriptionPlain": "*Think Ketchup is low in sugar? Think again!*\n\nA glazed donut has low sugar as compared to 3 tablespoons of ketchup!\nThe average serving of 3 tablespoons of ketchup typically contains up to 12g of sugar, While a glazed donut has approximately 10 grams of sugar. \n\nThis comparison highlights how easy it is to consume high amounts of sugar in unexpected ways.\n\nWhen switching to a healthy lifestyle, replace your ketchup with these two homemade alternatives!\nAnd you will find them there!\n\nThey both last around 4-6 days in the refrigerator. Sun-dried tomatoes are available at markets.\n\nHelpful tips on how to lose weight, restore your health & boost your immune system through the consumption of healthy foods!\n\n(healthy food) (sugar) (tomato ketchup) (glazed donut) (healthy lifestyle)",
