    "id": "710",
    "title": "10,000 steps (calorie burn)",
    "category": "Cardiac",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "“How Many Calories Do You Burn While Walking 10k Steps Each Day?”:\n\n10K step is a viral fitness & weight loss topic worldwide ✅\n\nWalking is a simple yet powerful way to boost your metabolism, improve heart health, and help with weight loss. \nThe calories burned can vary depending on factors like gender, weight, and walking speed. \n\nHere’s a closer look:\n\n✨ For a Person with Normal Weight (Approx. 60-70 kg)\nMen: \nOn average, a man weighing around 70 kg can burn approximately 400-500 calories. This varies depending on speed and terrain, but it’s a great daily calorie burn.\nWomen: \nA woman weighing around 60 kg might burn around 300-400 calories with 10k steps.\n\n✨ For an Overweight Individual (Approx. 85-100 kg)\n\nMen: \nIf you’re around 90-100 kg, walking 10k steps can burn anywhere from 500-700 calories. The heavier you are, the more calories you burn with each step due to the extra energy required to move your body.\n\nWomen: \nFor women in the 85-90 kg range, you can expect to burn around 400-600 calories. Walking is a low-impact exercise, making it perfect for those looking to ease into fitness while still burning fat.\n\n💡 What Affects Calorie Burn?\n\nSpeed: The faster you walk, the more calories you burn.\nIncline: Walking uphill or on rough terrain burns more calories than walking on flat surfaces.\nAge: Younger individuals tend to burn calories more efficiently than older adults, though walking remains an effective exercise at any age!\n\n Do you track your daily steps? Let me know in the comments below!👇",
