    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "5 diet TIPS for a perfect Karva Chauth Vrat!\n\nPre Dawn [Sargi]\n1. Because you will be fasting, load your nutrients smartly for the day!🤩\n\n2. Eat your sargi in the following order:\n- 1 Cup of coconut water to replenish and store your electrolyte levels, essential for fasting\n- Hydrating fruits like watermelon, orange, apple which are rich in fiber, water and postassium for energy\n- 1 source of fats from Nuts and seeds [2 walnuts/3 to 4 almonds]\n- A protein source\n- Last is your carbohydrate to midfully load for the fasting!\n\n3. Following a sequence of nutrients will help in managing blood glucose and energy levels till you break the fast without much muscle loss\n\n4. Enjoy your fasting hours with faith in your heart and a smile on your face😄\n\n5. When you break the fast, follow a smart sequence and be gentle to your tummy!\n\n6. Break your fast with a simple glass of coconut water to keep your headache away!\n\n- Replenish your glucose with an easy-to-digest carbohydrate like a date!\n\n- Make sure your meal is easy to digest yet adequate in fiber and proteins so that you don’t shoot your blood glucose as this stores more fats.\n\n- For the sake of your stomach and digestion, NEVER HOG ON LARGE AMOUNTS OF FOOD AFTER A FAST\n\n- Be gentle to your body after it is in a state of fast to allow it to take a limited nutrient load.\n\nHope you have a happy and healthy Karva Chauth! ✨🎑🌕\n\n( Karva Chauth, Fasting tips, Sargi, Nutrition)",
