    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Top 5 Veg Desi Foods to get your daily protein & calcium requirements. \n\nCalcium is a key building block for bones. But as we age, our bones lose calcium faster, making them fragile. Keeping up with calcium-rich foods can help reduce this loss, protecting against fractures and osteoporosis.\n\nProtein isn’t just for muscle—it’s critical for bone density too! It helps maintain bone mass and strengthens muscle tissues around the bones, which adds support and stability, reducing the risk of falls and fractures.\n\n🌿 Top 5 Desi Veg Sources of Protein & Calcium:\n\nRagi (Finger Millet) – This has more calcium than milk. Ragi upma with sprouts as breakfast is the best way to add this to your diet. \n\nChickpeas & Lentils – Loaded with protein to support bone structure.\nChole, Rajma, Dals & da chillas should be in added to 2 meals in a day. \n\nPaneer (Indian Cottage Cheese) – Offers both protein and calcium. Use the low fat & home made version to avoid excess calories. \n\nSesame Seeds (Til) – High in calcium and help reduce inflammation.\nAdd this to your roti, paratha or in your Tadka \n\nSoybeans – Full of protein, they’re a great meat-free source. Please try having tofu bhurji at least once every alternate day to your meals. \n\n(Osteoarthritis, osteoporosis, high protein diet, high calcium diet, vegetarian protein)",
