    "id": "703",
    "title": "3 foods to avoid",
    "category": "Cardiac",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "3 Foods to Avoid Every Festive Season ✨\n\n\t1.\tSoan Papdi\n\t•\tLoaded with Hydrogenated Fat: High in trans fats, which raise “bad” cholesterol (LDL) and increase heart disease risk.\n\t•\tQuestionable Production Quality: Often made in unsanitary conditions, increasing the risk of contamination.\n\t•\tExcess Sugar & Calories: Causes quick energy spikes and crashes, making it harder to control cravings.\n\n\t2.\tArtificially Flavored & Colored Mithai\n\t•\tHigh in Artificial Colors & Additives: Colors like Red #40 and Yellow #5 may trigger digestive issues and allergic reactions.\n\t•\tRefined Sugars & Chemical Additives: Put extra strain on the liver, making it harder for your body to detoxify and stay balanced.\n\t•\tMinimal Nutritional Value: These desserts often lack fiber or protein, leaving you feeling unsatisfied.\n\n\t3.\tCoke, Pepsi & Other Aerated Drinks\n\t•\tEmpty Calories & High Sugar Content: With zero nutrients, these drinks are just sugar and calories, promoting weight gain and fat accumulation.\n\t•\tTriggers Cravings: The sugar rush spikes dopamine, increasing cravings for more sweets and junk foods.\n\t•\tImpacts Bone Health: Phosphoric acid in Coke can interfere with calcium absorption, weakening bones over time.\n\nWishing you all a healthy & prosperous Diwali! 🎉\n\n( Festive season, Diwali, Healthy eating, Nutritional value, Food choices )",
    "tags": [
      "HealthyDiwali",
      "FestiveEats",
      "FoodAwareness",
      "HealthTips",
      "CelebrateWisely",
      "KhyatiRupani",
      "BalanceNutrition"
    ],
    "instagramUrl": "https://www.instagram.com/reel/DByWvx0S9JD/?igsh=endsMXp3aWJmY3o%3D",
