    "descriptionPlain": "BN Gut Reset Challenge Tip 2:\n\nThe right cooking oil & dietary fat play a vital role in ensuring good gut health. This also aids weight loss, corrects hormonal imbalances, and reduces inflammation.\n\n The 3 oils and fats that are beneficial for your gut are\n—coconut oil, ghee, and butter!\n\n Coconut oil: Rich in MCTs, promotes beneficial gut bacteria and boosts metabolism. \nGhee: Full of butyrate to strengthen the gut lining and reduce inflammation. \nGrass-fed butter: Packed with CLA, known for its anti-inflammatory benefits.\n\nTips for Best Results:\n1. Use pure coconut oil for cooking, not cold-pressed.\n2. Use homemade ghee instead of store-bought.\n3. Homemade Indian Makkhan is way better than packaged salted butter. \n4. Use oils & fats sparingly if you are overweight or obese\n\n(Best oils, weight loss, gut health, ghee, coconut oil, butter)",
