    "id": "625",
    "title": "Chocolate day reel",
    "category": "PCOS",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Comment ‘YES’ if you’re ready to start your fat-loss journey the right way!\n\nWhen I lost 40 kg, I realized that weight loss was never about obsessively weighing food, counting every calorie, or eliminating entire food groups. Instead, what truly helped me shed body fat—especially belly fat—was identifying and fixing these three key mistakes in my diet.\n\nBacked by scientific research, these small but impactful changes can help you lose weight without frustration!\n\nMISTAKE 1: Obsessing Over Calories\nI used to count every single calorie, which left me frustrated and made me hate food. I went off track multiple times and ended up bingeing.\n\nInstead of calorie counting, focus on portion control—it’s far more sustainable!\n\nMISTAKE 2: Ignoring Liquid Calories\nDrinks like milkshakes, sodas, frappes, and even fruit juices can unknowingly add up to 2,000 extra calories a day! Cutting down on these made a massive difference in my fat loss.\n\nMISTAKE 3 (The Biggest One!): Over-Restricting My Favorite Foods\nI used to have chocolate after every meal but decided to eliminate it completely. That backfired! Instead, I made smarter swaps:\n\n✅ Switched from high-sugar milk chocolate to dark chocolate\n✅ Ate half a piece instead of two\n✅ Limited it to two meals per week instead of daily\n✅ Reduced intake gradually, not abruptly\n\nSustainable weight loss isn’t about extreme restriction—it’s about balance!\n\n(Chocolate Day, Balance diet, Portion control, Weightloss)",
