    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Comment ‘Rose’ if you need help in losing weight\n\nFeeling bloated or uncomfortable? Try this soothing Rose Petal Fennel Detox Tea for instant relief!\n\nRose Petal Fennel Detox Tea\n(Instant bloating relief, gut-friendly, anti-inflammatory)\n\nIngredients:\n1 tbsp dried rose petals\n1 tsp fennel seeds (saunf)\n½ tsp carom seeds (ajwain)\n1-inch piece fresh ginger (grated)\n1.5 cups water\n\nHow to Make It:\n1. Bring 1.5 cups of water to a boil in a pan.\n2. Add fennel seeds, carom seeds, and grated ginger. Simmer on low heat.\n3. Turn off the heat and add dried rose petals. Cover and let it steep for 5 minutes.\n4. Strain and serve.\n\nHow It Works:\nRose petals soothe digestion, reduce inflammation, and relax stomach muscles, while fennel seeds effectively combat gas and bloating.\n\nIdeal Time to Drink This Tea:\nPost-meal (30–45 minutes after eating): Aids digestion, prevents bloating, and reduces inflammation.\nFor chronic bloating/inflammation: Best consumed in the morning on an empty stomach.\nAt night: Helps relax digestion and reduce nighttime bloating.\n\nHow Many Days Should You Have It?\nFor long-term anti-inflammatory benefits: Drink 5 days a week for a month, then as needed.\n\n(Roseday, Health, nutrition, valentineweek, Healthylife)",
