    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "The Link Between Ozempic, Mounjaro & Thyroid Cancer Risk: What We Need to Know\n\nNew research has linked popular weight-loss injections like Ozempic, Wegovy, and Mounjaro to a higher risk of thyroid cancer.\n\nA study of 350,000+ patients found that the likelihood of thyroid cancer was significantly higher within the first year of use.\n\n📌 Key Findings:\n✔️ Research on rodents previously suggested a link between semaglutide (Ozempic, Wegovy) and medullary thyroid cancer (MTC).\n✔️ This new study, tracking patients for six years, found a higher incidence of thyroid cancer.\n\n⚠️ My Concerns as a Nutritionist:\n\n1. I have had clients who developed thyroid cancer while using these injections.\n2. Female clients have experienced an increase in fibroids.\n3. A link between these injections and hysterectomy has also been observed.\n4. High usage of these drugs is seen in places where insurance covers them, implying economic benefits for many.\n\nWould I recommend these injections for diabetes or weight loss?\nNO.\n\nWhether it is diabetes or obesity, simple changes in your diet and lifestyle are key to controlling—and even reversing—diabetes.\n\nTried and tested drugs should be used with caution under the supervision of expert doctors for uncontrolled diabetes.",
