    "id": "576",
    "title": "Tahira Kashyap fights with cancer",
    "category": "General",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "When life challenges you again & again, you either break or rise. Tahira Kashyap? She rises with grace, grit, and grounded wisdom. \n\nAs a nutritionist, I see her battle with cancer not just as one of resilience but as a living testament to the powerful link between self-awareness, early detection, and whole-body wellness.\n\nCancer isn’t just a physical battle it’s a lifestyle wake-up call. \n\nTahira’s courage to share her journey publicly, as she enters Round 2, is not only brave, it’s transformative. \nShe’s reframing illness as a chance to reconnect with our bodies, habits, and health. And one thing she drives home? Early detection is everything. \n\nRegular mammograms aren’t an option; they’re an act of self-love. \n\nHer metaphor is perfect: “When life throws lemons... add kala khatta and sip it with good intentions.” \n\nAs someone who works closely with individuals on healing from the inside out, I’ve seen how whole-food nutrition, anti-inflammatory habits, and emotional wellbeing all support recovery not just from disease, but from stress, fatigue, and the silent wear-and-tear we often ignore.\n\nTahira’s story isn’t just inspiring, it’s instructional. It’s a call for all of us to listen more closely to our bodies, to choose food that fuels us, habits that heal us, and screenings that could save us.\n\nSo let this be a moment not just of admiration, but of action. Start with your plate. Start with your calendar. Start with yourself.",
