    "id": "574",
    "title": "How to eat pav baji without guilt?",
    "category": "PCOS",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "As a nutritionist, I get asked this all the time: “Do I have to give up my favorite Indian street foods to eat healthy?”\nAnd my answer? Absolutely NOT.\n\nPav Bhaji is a gorgeous blend of vegetables, spices, and pure comfort.\n\nHere’s my step-by-step hack to enjoy your favorite bhaji without the guilt:\n\n1️⃣ Start with a warm, clear vegetable soup. Don’t touch the bhaji until it’s finished!\n2️⃣ Have half of your green salad before diving into the bhaji! \n3️⃣ Top your bhaji with chaas instead of buttered pavs. You’ll eat less and feel fuller.\n4️⃣ When you’re ready, try ordering your pav without butter. Trust me, small changes make a BIG difference!\n\nYou’re not just cutting calories — you’re nourishing your body, boosting digestion, and still enjoying every bite. Step by step, healthier habits win!",
