    "id": "558",
    "title": "One Liner",
    "category": "Gut Health",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "YOU DONT WANNA MISS THIS👇🏻\n\nBut first, LIKE & FOLLOW for daily fitness tips✨\n\n5 Things to Do After a High-Calorie Meal (Backed by Science & Practical Tips)\n\n1️⃣Go for a Walk (10-15 Minutes Post-Meal)\n\nStudies show that a 10-15 minute walk after eating can lower post-meal blood glucose spikes, especially after a carb-heavy meal.\n\n✅eg. If you had a bug Indian thali or a pizza binge, take a brisk walk around your home or office instead of sitting down immediately. Even light household chores count!\n\n2️⃣Hydrate Well (Flush Out Excess Sodium & Aid Digestion)\n\nHigh-calorie meals often come with excess salt, fat & refined carbs, which can lead to bloating & water retention. Drinking 500-700mL of water post meal can help restore balance.\n\n3️⃣Make Your Next Meal Lighter (Balance It Out)\n\n Instead of feeling guilty and skipping meals, focus on protein, fibre and water-rich foods in your next meal to stabilise hunger & metabolism.\n\n✅eg. If you had a ghee masala dosa with coconut chutney, make your next meal lighter with a protein-rich salad or dal soup.\n\n4️⃣Avoid Overcompensating\n\nMany people try to “undo” a high-calorie meal by starving themselves of over-exercising.\n\n✅eg. If you overate at a wedding buffet, don’t skip breakfast the next day. Instead, opt for boiled moong chaat or a simple dal-chawal meal to keep your metabolism steady.\n\n5️⃣Get Enough Sleep\n\nPoor sleep can worsen bloating, increase cravings & impact metabolism. After a high-calorie meal, your body is processing excess energy, & quality sleep helps regulate hunger hormones like lepton & ghrelin.\n\n✅eg. If you’ve indulged in a big dinner, avoid late-night snacking & sleep for atleast 7-8 hours.\n\nOne heavy meal doesn’t mean all progress is lost! Instead of guilt-tripping, focus on movement, hydration, mindful eating & consistency.\n\n📌Save this post for the next time you overeat.\n\n(Fitness tips, weight loss, healthy habits, post-binge recovery, mindful eating, calorie balance, fitness mindset)",
