    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "I am 41 years old, practicing nutrition for 19 years… and I’m not afraid to admit that:\n\n🔹 Studying nutrition wasn’t my first choice—I was just killing time, waiting to get accepted for MBBS. Life had other plans. All for the best.\n🔹 I was careless about my weight & health and hit 85+ kg at 25, shamefully calling myself a dietitian.\n🔹 PCOS & infertility were my only motivation to lose weight & take a hard look at what I was doing to my health —it was a wake-up call.\n🔹 Losing 40 kg twice has made me a better dietitian today—I understand the struggle firsthand. It made me dig deeper in the science & blend it with practical solutions avoiding failure.\n🔹 My husband is the reason for my success—without him, I would’ve settled for a simple job, never realizing my true potential.\n🔹 My daughter keeps me going every day—I feel like a teenager with her, ready to take on high school & all that comes with it together.\n🔹 I can’t stand people who don’t give 100% to their work—passion and commitment matter!\n\n(Fitness tips, weight loss, healthy habits, pcos, mindful eating, workout motivation, gym tips, strength training, fitness mindset)",
