    "id": "555",
    "title": "Rohan Mirchandani",
    "category": "Cardiac",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Rohan Mirchandani, co-founder of Epigamia, sadly passed away at just 42 years of age due to a cardiac arrest. \n\nHe was known to be quite active, with an interest in basketball. The company he founded also made Greek yogurt, which is healthy and high-protein.\n\nHeart attacks in people aged 25-44 have surged by 30% in just three years. I personally lost a very close family member to the same cause a few months ago. He too was healthy, ate clean, was slim, and fairly active.\n\nThe easiest thing to do is link it to chronic work stress and get away with it.\n\nIn my opinion, there are a lot of other factors that could contribute to sudden cardiac arrests, such as:\n1. Excessive gymming and physical activity,\n2. Sleep deprivation and late-night screen time,\n3. Not listening to the body and mind when they are tired,\n4. Overfeeding the body with packaged foods (especially those that call themselves healthy and mislead),\n5. Ignoring symptoms like gastric troubles, arm and shoulder pain,\n6. Overthinking,\n7. Over-analyzing,\n8. Taking supplements without any prescription.\n\nAt times, I always think that life is what we make of it. It is always OUR CHOICE, whether it’s the amount of stress we take or the food and lifestyle choices we make.\n\nI am going to read up and do in-depth research on this for the next few months. Hoping to write something more substantial then.\n\nWhat do you think is the most overlooked factor contributing to the rise in sudden cardiac arrests among young individuals?",
