    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "How Many Calories in Your Idli-Sambar Meal? 🥥🍛\n\nIdli Sambar is the most popular South Indian breakfast eaten by nearly every Indian at least once a week, but is it weight loss-friendly? \n\nA typical meal of Idli Sambar will comprise at least: \n\n🍽 4 Idlis (100 kcal each) = 400 kcal\n🍲 1 bowl of Sambar = 250 kcal\n🥥 1 katori of Coconut Chutney = 200 kcal‼️\nTotal = 850 kcal\n\nBut what if we could enjoy this comforting meal with fewer calories?\n\nThis is how you need to arrange your \n\n🍽 2 Idlis (100 kcal each) = 200 kcal\n🍲 1 bowl of Sambar (no coconut) = 100 kcal\n🌱 Mint Chutney = only 50 kcal\nTotal = 350 kcal\n\nTo lose weight, replace the coconut chutney & reduce the Idlis. \n\nP.S. If still hungry, add a bowl of coconut free sambar or green veggies to your meal. \n\nWill you follow this Health Tip?",
