    "descriptionPlain": "Let’s break it down!\n\n**🍽 Nutritional Breakdown:**\n\n**Greek Yogurt (100g):**\n- **Calories:** 120\n- **Protein:** 8g\n\n**Indian Curd (100g):**\n- **Calories:** 98\n- **Protein:** 11g\n\n**🌟 Benefits of Indian Curd Over Greek Yogurt:**\n\n- **Probiotics Powerhouse:** Indian curd is rich in natural probiotics that improve gut health and digestion.\n\n- **Cooling Effect:** Naturally cools the body, making it perfect for summer!\n\n- **Affordable & Accessible:** Easily available and budget-friendly. Where Greek yogurt can cost Rs.90/100g, you can get curd at Rs.10/100g \n\nIt is also higher in protein, easier to digest.\n\nWhen you are reading about greek yoghurt being high in protein, the comparison is based on yoghurt and not Indian curd.\nDo you use expensive greek yoghurt at home?\n\nYes \nNo",
