    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "All you need to know about cholesterol, oils, and fats!\n\nWatch the Video Carefully to remember which oils are to be used according to the dish you make.\n\nImportant points to remember:\n\n👉 All oils are cholesterol-free - Cholesterol is a substance that is found only in animals. Your milk and curd will have cholesterol whereas sunflower oil will not because it is from a plant.\n\n👉 Plant sources have other fats - Oils that come from plants have fatty acids and triglycerides. These are a type of fat and very different from cholesterol. So you have to have them sparingly as well.\n\n👉 Cholesterol is saturated fat. So all oils are naturally free from cholesterol.\n\n👉 PUFA & MUFA are fatty acids that are found in oils and other plant sources. These are unsaturated fats.\n\n👉 Trans fats are extremely harmful - These are artificial fats like vanaspati ghee and margarine.",
