    "id": "531",
    "title": "Does refrigerated rice have less calories?",
    "category": "Diabetes",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Refrigerated rice does not contribute to the instant rise in sugar levels, but it contributes less and very slowly to the rise in blood sugar levels due to the presence of resistant starch.\n\nFresh rice contains more carbohydrates and, hence, more GI and GL value than cooled and reheated rice.\n\nHence, cooled and reheated rice should be preferred more to fresh rice to prevent the increased spike in the blood glucose levels in the body.\n\nBut this doesn’t mean it has reduced calories or will help you lose weight if eaten in huge portions.\n\nThis rice needs to be eaten with fresh veggies, dal, chicken & in portions to see weight loss!",
