    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Peanut butter is a relatively unprocessed food if made at home. It’s just peanuts, often roasted, ground until they turn into a paste.\n\nThis isn’t necessarily true for many commercial brands of peanut butter. These contain various added ingredients, such as:\n\nSugar\nVegetable oils\nTrans fat\n\nAnd eating too much-added sugar and trans fat has been linked to various health conditions, such as heart disease.\n\nTwo tablespoons (32 grams) of natural peanut butter include: Calories: 190.\nProtein: 8 grams.\nFat: 16 grams.\n\nThis is very high amount of calories and fat, given the small volume of food & may not be considered an ideal option for your weight loss goals.",
