    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Here are a few ways you can avoid mindless eating or snacking -\n\n• Acknowledge the importance of snacks for a healthy meal routine. Don’t deprive yourself of your favourite foods. It will lead to a lot of overthinking & munching. \n\n• Make a proper snack time in your schedule. Ask your dietitian to add meal options. \n\n• Plan healthy snacks during meal prep to avoid overeating and to get in tune with your hunger cues.\n\n• Control your portion and savour every bite. Eat slowly. \n\n• Create a healthy work environment when you are eating, avoid distractions like screen time or engaging in a conversation.\n\nChoose low calorie or zero calorie foods like cucumber, puffed rice, carrot sticks, roasted chana and fresh fruit bites.",
