    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Eliminate oral bacteria – While brushing your teeth with neem twigs, you have to chew their tender barks. The antibacterial juice produced in this activity will flow into your mouth. It helps in killing the harmful microorganisms in your mouth.\n\nNatural toothache reliever – Similar to stopping bacteria growth, neem sticks are powerful to soothe the throbbing nerves underneath a tooth. Hence it is considered a natural remedy to treat toothache. If you sense an aching feeling in a tooth, take a need twig. Bite and chew its corner with the problematic tooth. It will help you in overcoming the pain\n\nStrengthen the gums – Researches show that chewing neem sticks can improve the immune response in gums and teeth. It can safeguard the gum tissues hence that the chances of plaque build-up and gum infections can be reduced to a great extent. \n\nHelps in teeth whitening – Besides antibacterial and anti-fungal agents, the active compounds released while chewing neem sticks have whitening properties also. It means that brushing your teeth with neem twigs would remove enamel stains and discolorations.\n\nApart from neem twigs, chewing neem leaves is also helpful in keeping the alkaline level in your saliva. It inhibits the growth of potentially dangerous oral bacteria.\n\nWill you try this tooth brush? Tell us in comments!",
