    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Masala Kaju has always been a Diwali favorite! But be careful as it can quickly add to your weight gain 😁\n\nNuts, whether raw or masala-coated, are calorie-dense. Here’s why plain & unsalted cashews are a healthier choice:\n\n• Lower Calories: Raw cashews naturally contain fewer calories than masala-fried versions.\n• Reduced Fat: Fried cashews come with added oils, raising both fat and calorie content.\n• No Added Sodium: Plain cashews are free from the extra salt used in masala seasoning.\n• Better Nutrient Retention: Raw cashews retain more nutrients since they aren’t exposed to high-heat frying.\n\nP.S. Limit yourself to 8-10 nuts a day this festive season.\n\n(Diwali treats, Nut nutrition, Healthy snacking, Healthy fats, Portion control)",
