    "id": "517",
    "title": "When I stopped making these 3 diet mistakes, my weight dropped faster!",
    "category": "PCOS",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "While losing 40 kg, I realised that it was never about weighing your food, counting your calories, managing your meals on time or eliminating foods.\n\nWhat helped me the most to get rid of body fat & belly fat was realising these 3 mistakes I was making with my food.\n\nIt is also backed by a lot of scientific research, and there is also evidence that you can lose weight with these changes in your day to day diet.\n\nMISTAKE 1:\n\nI was trying to count my calories.\nWhile it is necessary to understand the rough estimate of calories, I did it for every morsel of food. It was getting me frustrated & I started hating food overall.\nI went off track many times & cheated.\n\nMore than calories, it is important to understand portion size.\n\nMISTAKE 2:\n\nNot estimating liquid calories.\n\nYou can add 2000 cal in your daily diet by consuming a milkshake, cold drinks, frappes & fruit juice.\n\nMISTAKE 3:\nConfusing thirst with hunger.\n\nMany of us don’t realise that the body is thirsty, not hungry. This is because of ignoring the thirst signals body was sending us. Now, the thirst signal gets impaired. Leads to excessive consumption of food.\n\nIf you are hungry, have water first, then go for food.\n\n(counting your calories) (weight loss) (day-to-day diet) (body fat & belly fat) (healthy food) (fruit juice) (hunger)",
