    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "A few years ago, we as nutrition experts weren’t big fans of diet colas. For a lot of us, these are artificially sweetened & contained aspartame!\nBang - theory tells us it causes cancer & is harmful. So we banned it from the diets of our clients.\n\nLike most of you go to Google & see how they can turn a simple cold symptom to pneumonia, we too read up things that were printed in our journals.\n\nWhen I read about carcinogens recently, I figured that they have categories & aspartame falls in level 2B. It says this could be possibly carcinogenic. This list has 94 other foods which include aloe vera, pickled vegetables & more.\n\nSo, having a glass of diet Coke instead of regular Coke is a much better idea to have the diet versions instead.\n\n1 glass diet coke = 0 calories & 0g Sugar\n1 glass regular coke = 150 calories & 30g sugar‼️\n\n(nutrition) (diet cola) (calorie content) (sugar content) (comparison) (health concerns) (cancer risk) (parents) (artificial sweeteners)",
