    "id": "505",
    "title": "When someone says I don't eat carbs still I am not losing",
    "category": "PCOS",
    "subType": "General",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Carbs Ki Kahani 🧐\n\nMost of us think their weight issues are only because of carbs! Roti & rice bandh karna hai bas!\n\nFACTS:\n\nNot getting enough carbs can be bad. Eating too many carbs is bad. What does a person do? 🤷🏻‍♀\n\nMany people reduce carbohydrate intake to help them lose weight, which shouldn't be a concern at all!!!!\n\nCarbohydrates are the most efficient fuel for the brain, the internal functions of the body as well as a very healthy source of energy.\n\nWestern diets swear by high protein as they always are meat-eaters. High fat in meats has harmful effects on cardiac health.\n\nOn the other hand, diets rich in fibre and complex carbs always prove to be safer, healthier and have high satiety making one feel full for long.\n\nSo avoid simple sugars, potatoes, pressure-cooked white rice, refined flour, sago in case you want to lose weight and stick to oats, millets instead.\n\nThe right carbs are your friends in weight loss.",
