    "descriptionPlain": "When on a diet, should we avoid tea or no?\n\nA cup of tea with 1 teaspoon of sugar contains 45 to 60 cal.\n\nIf it is masala tea, then the benefits of ginger, cardamom, cloves and cinnamon are an added advantage.\n\nThe most common snack had with Tea are,\nBiscuits: 100 calories \nChivda: 200 calories \nWada pav: 200 calories \nMathri: 300 calories \nCookies: 300 calories\n\nThese calories are not even Healthy calories and contain only sugar and fat.\n\nHence, it is not the tea but the accompaniment we usually have with it that causes weight gain.\n\nHealthy accompaniments with Tea are: \nDiet khakhra: 40 calories \nMakhana(plain): 50 calories \nBhel: 100 calories",
