    "title": "Me: I'll strictly follow my diet from today. Also Me: 30 mins later..",
    "category": "General",
    "subType": "General",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "When you were super motivated starting your diet but by the time you get lunch you regret your whole life 😂\n\n How will the diet be?? Too strict?\n\nMy take -\nA good dietitian takes into consideration a lot of factors before chalking out a chart. Most important are a client’s ethnic, geographical and lifestyle preferences. \n\nA client living alone in the USA or the Middle East will not be able to cope with a hot fresh Indian breakfast, or roti sabzi dal lunch.... so it is very necessary to take a look at stores and foods available around to make a sensible and practical chart.\n\nIndia is a very diverse country and the foods vary from region to religion - a south Indian can’t imagine his diet without rice whereas a north Indian will never be able to follow a soup and salad meal.\n\nWe have got the best results in clients where we have followed the above principles ✅",
