    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Best oil for cooking can’t be just 1 - based on the smoke point, the oil needs to change while cooking different kinds of food.\n\nIf you are trying to lose weight or maintain your body fat, then use minimal oil & ghee in your tempering. \n\n*Ghee or Unrefined Oil (Dal Tadka):* \n- High in fats that help the body absorb nutrients better. \n- Gives satiety and has fat-soluble vitamins too.\n- ⁠it has a high smoke point making it a better choice\n\n*Sesame Oil (Asian Dishes)* :\n\n- Heart health is supported by the high antioxidant content.\n \n- ⁠High smoke point too. \n\n*Coconut Oil:* \n\n- Rich in medium-chain triglycerides (MCTs) making it easier to digest than other oils.\n- Accelerates metabolic rate. \n\n(unrefined oil) ( healthy meal) (healthy life) (cholesterol) (low calorie) (high protein) (good food good mood)",
