    "id": "453",
    "title": "I started losing weight a lot faster after changing this 1 thing in my diet!",
    "category": "Diabetes",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "While losing 40 kg, I realised that it was never about weighing your food, counting your calories, managing your meals on time or eliminating foods.\n\nWhat helped me the most was this 1 hack.\n\nIt is also backed by a lot of scientific research, and there is also evidence that you can lose weight, especially body fat with this particular change in your day to day diet. \n\nThe star of the show here is fiber.\n\nI am aware of the current protein talk that is making rounds all over Social Media.\n\nWhile there is no denial in protein and its importance, an overweight person needs to be adding fibre to the diet.\n\nWhat is fibre? \n\nFiber is a type of carbohydrate that the body can’t digest. Fiber cannot be broken down into sugar & passes through the body undigested. \n\nFiber regulates the body’s use of sugars, helping to keep hunger & blood sugar & cholesterol in check.\n\nWe need 30-35 g of fiber per day, but get only about 15 g! \n\nOnce we fix this, weight loss is bound to happen.\n\nWhat did I do to get this right?\n\nI simply started all my meals with fibre.\n\nIn breakfast, I added oats or apple along with boiled egg whites. No breads.\n\nLunch & dinner always started with a salad. I included brown rice or millet Roti instead of white rice or wheat phulka. \n\nP.S - if you are not careful about your water intake, this could cause constipation. So stay hydrated.\n\n(Weight loss) (Fiber intake) (Hydration) (Meal structure) (Carbohydrate) (Protein)",
