    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Facts about Weight Training & Weight Loss-\n\nMost trainers are at war with dietitians as we recommend weight training only after the client loses some weight while they advocate weight training immediately.\n\nWhether you should do weights or not depends on-\n\n1. Goal: If you are looking to lose weight on the weighing scale & want to bring down the weight from 80 to 70 kg, then weight training may not be ideal for you. \n\nAs explained in the Video, you will need to perform LSAT. \n\n2. Bulk Up: If your goal is to gain muscle mass, not to get weight loss on the scale, then you can do weight training. \n\nSo, be wise & pick your exercise choices 😃\n\nWhile hitting the weights is undoubtedly beneficial, achieving weight loss goals requires a comprehensive approach. Here's the lowdown:\n\n🍽️ Your Diet Matters: Aim for a diet that's rich in fiber and low in fat. And for even better results, try this plan: Long, Sustainable, Aerobic, and Training.\n\nRemember, sustainable weight loss isn't achieved overnight. It's a journey that requires dedication, consistency, and a holistic approach.\n\n(weight loss) (weight training) (health) (fat loss) (trending) (healthy food)",
