    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Eid Mubarak from Balance Nutrition! Wishing you a healthy and nourishing celebration! 💯 \n\nCheck out our nutritious recipes for guilt-free indulgence - \n1. Sugar Free Apple Cookies\nIngredients - \nRolled oats - 1 tbsp \nUnsweetened peanut butter - 1 tbsp\nWalnuts (crushed) - 1 tsp\nCinnamon powder - 1 tsp\nApple - 1 medium\n\nMethod - \nCombine the oats and cinnamon in a dry skillet over medium heat and toast, stirring occasionally, until the oats are golden. Cool before using.\nCore and slice the apple into 6 rounds.\nSpread 1 tbsp of peanut butter on 3 of the apple slices and sprinkle with walnuts and oats.\nTop with the remaining apple slices to form sandwiches.\n\n2. Split Banana Coco Bites \nIngredients - \nBanana Medium - 1 no.\nMuesli - 1 tbsp\nChocolate Syrup - 1 tbsp\nPeanut Butter - 2 tsp\n\nMethod - \nTake 1 banana and cut it vertically into 2 halves\nApply 1 tsp of peanut butter on each slice.\nAdd some muesli and drizzle chocolate syrup on top of it.\n\n3. Fruit Bowl for Pre-Diabetics \nIngredients - \nLow-fat yogurt - ¾ bowl\nMuesli - 2 tsp\nApple - 3 tbsp chopped\nAny fruit of your choice - 3 tsp\nWalnuts - 1tsp. [crushed]\nRaisins - 1 tsp\n\nMethod - \nLayer 1/3rd cup of low-fat yogurt into the bottom of a tall glass.\nPut a layer of chopped apple, alternately with yogurt and the fruit of your choice until glasses are filled to the top. \nAdd muesli on the top layer with crushed walnuts and raisins. \nServe parfaits immediately to relish the yummy taste.\n\n[balanced eating] [eid mubarak] [nutrition] [festive treats]",
