    "descriptionPlain": "5 Indian street food that you can have when on a diet!\n\nChana Chaat: a cheap, high protein, low fat snack, that you can get easily in most parts of our country.\n\nDry Bhel: very low-fat. If you skip the sev and low carb if you replace the potatoes with sprouts or roasted chana. This is also very filling as a big portion of dry bhel has barely any calories.\n\nMoongdal Chilla: The protein content of 1 besan chilla is almost 7.86g, added benefit for vegetarians looking for a protein-rich diet. \n\n Idli Sambar: This is the staple breakfast of most Indians across the country. It is rich in probiotics and also protein. Low in calories and if you skip the coconut Chutney, it is low in fat as well.\n\nMumbai Sandwich: Dirch the white bread and opt for whole wheat or multigrain. Tell him to skip the butter and the potatoes.\n\n*exercise caution & prioritize hygiene before you choose the option*",
