    "descriptionPlain": "Nut Milk vs. Regular Milk: Which is Better? \n\nMany of us are moving to nut milk & oat milk instead of regular animal milk that we have had for centuries. \nEver wondered about the calorie content & other parameters of your milk choices? \n\nLet’s break it down & understand better.\n In 100ml of cow’s milk, you’ll find approximately 42 calories, while the same amount of almond or soy milk contains around 40-50 calories. Surprised? Don’t be! \nMost kinds of milk, except full-fat buffalo milk offer similar calorie counts. \nPlus, cow’s milk contains about 3.25g of fat and 12mg of cholesterol per 100ml, more or less similar to nut milk variations.\n\nBut here’s the kicker: while nut milk boasts health benefits, be wary of added preservatives like carrageenan, guar gum, and xanthan gum. \nMost nut milks are primarily water with nuts comprising only about 5% of the ingredients. Watch out for those additives. \n\nP.S. If you are not lactose intolerant & have access to unadulterated fresh milk, pick the low-fat version if this one. \nIt has highly bioavailable calcium, class 1 protein & also Fat-soluble vitamins A, D, E & K.\nSo, if you’re on a weight loss journey, choose either with caution!",
