    "id": "429",
    "title": "Common mistakes at Iftar that have a negative impact on health & weight loss:",
    "category": "PCOS",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Common mistakes at Iftar that have a negative impact on health & weight loss:\n\n❌ Drinking large amounts of water at Iftar time\n\n✔️ IMPACT: Filling the stomach with water is more strenuous to it than with food.\n\nSolution: Can have few sips during Iftar. Later, a glass full of water every two hours.\n\n❌ Drinking Roohafza on daily basis\n\n✔️ IMPACT: It contains high amounts of added sugars, preservatives, and food colors.\n\nSolution: Can be consumed twice a week if required.\n\n❌ Chewing and swallowing food quickly\n\n✔️ IMPACT: Increases unhealthy weight gain and slows down the digestion process.\n\nSolution: Chewing food slowly will speed up digestion and helps in maintaining a healthy weight.\n\n❌ Consuming foods high in sodium\n\n✔️ IMPACT: Sodium triggers thirst through out the fasting hours of the day.\n\nSolution: Consume foods dense in potassium as they retain water and suppress thirst. Banana can be consumed during Suhoor, so as to control thirst levels throughout the day. Other foods such as milk, dates, avocados, pistachios, dried peaches, pumpkin, peas and dark chocolates (in minimum amounts) can be consumed.\n\n❌ Intake of sweets/desserts soon after Iftar\n\n✔️ IMPACT: Leaves you feeling drowsy and sleepy. \n\nSolution: Wait for two hours of having an Iftar meal to stay fresh and awake for Isha Prayers.\n\n❌ Exercising directly after Iftar\n\n✔️ IMPACT: Adverse effects on blood flow as it is concentrated around the stomach during Iftar. \n\nSolution: To ease digestion, work out after two hours of intake.\n\nTo know more about our Diet programs Call/ WhatsApp:\nNutritionist Vaishnavi: 9820017056\nNutritionist Aayushi: 9152419847",
