    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "TO EXERCISE OR NOT TO EXERCISE?????\n\nMany of our future members (i like to call those who inquire with us this) ask me, “Khyati, is your program only diet or is there a compulsory exercise?”\n\nKhyati says, “ I see you are super busy with your day, you hardly seem to have time to commit to any form of physical activity. \n\nMoreover, if I make it compulsory for you to exercise AND follow a diet, you’ll end up frustrated and hate me and diet & exercise. \n\nSo, let’s be realistic and start with ONE step at a time!”\n\nI have also noticed people who exercise tend to feel they can sneak in that piece of cake or a samosa as they burnt 450 calories... NO! \n\nYou can’t.... Similarly, you can’t OUT EXERCISE a bad meal you had the next day by doing 20 extra minutes.\n\nAs for any weight loss/fitness program, food plays an 80% role & exercising can accelerate the process as you burn more calories.\n\nGive 100% efforts to control 1 aspect of weight loss then add another.",
