    "id": "387",
    "title": "Until necessary, Ketchups are best avoided",
    "category": "General",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Side effects of ketchup are often neglected by its users. Tomato ketchup is a sauce used as a condiment. \n\nThe main ingredients of tomato ketchup besides tomatoes are sugar, salt & preservatives.\n\nHome-made ketchups also contain high amounts of salt & sugar making it a very unhealthy addition to our diet.\n\nLet’s see the top side effects of ketchup:\n\n👉🏻 Acid reflux\nTomatoes are also rich in citric and malic acid. When too much of these substances accumulate in your stomach, it will cause heartburn or acid reflux.\n\n👉🏻 Allergic reactions\nConsuming food that is rich in this compound leads to the development of rashes. It also causes allergic reactions. \n\n👉🏻 Joint Pain\nIt is rich in solanine. This is a compound that builds up calcium in the tissues. Excess amounts thereof cause inflammation and body pains.\n\n👉🏻 Diarrhea\nRaw tomatoes are susceptible to salmonella contamination which causes diarrhea.\n\n👉🏻 Kidney Stone\nSince the fruit is rich in oxalate and calcium, it is not easily broken down if you consume excessive amounts of these nutrients possibly lead to the formation of kidney stones.",
