    "descriptionPlain": "Most of us think a diabetic cannot have coconut water & that it will have an impact on their blood sugars. \n\nHowever, here are some facts about coconut water:\n\n1. Coconut water has a low glycemic index and contains a very low amount of natural sugar which doesn’t lead to a spike in your glucose levels.\n\n2. With low sugar content, coconut water is suitable for people with diabetes. \n\n3. Coconut water in fact helps control blood sugar thanks to its high content of potassium, manganese, magnesium, vitamin C, and L - arginine.\n\nIMPORTANT TIP:\n If you are thirsty, in need of a refreshing drink & craving cola or juice, this is a far better alternative. \n\nBe sure to choose an unsweetened variety and limit your intake to 1–2 cups (240–280 ml) per day.\n\nFor uncontrolled & very high blood sugar, add 1 tsp of chia seeds to the coconut water, let them swell up for 30 min, add a pinch of cinnamon powder & have.",
