    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "WHITE RICE Vs BROWN RICE 🍚 \n\nLet’s put an end to this shall we?\n\n👉 White Rice \n\nWhite Rice Is good Source of Vitamin B1 & B3\n\nMilling & polishing removes the most of the fiber\n\nIt is Low in Potassium & Contains 50% less Manganese and Iron\n\nIncreases the risk of Type 2 Diabetes & high cholesterol\n\nMay cause weight gain\n\n👉 Brown Rice\n\nExcellent source of Vitamin B1 & B3\n\nGood source of dietary fiber & Contains Potassium.\n\nFat found is heart friendly & is Rich source of Manganese\n\nReduces risk of Type 2 Diabetes & Controls blood cholesterol \n\nHelps in weight loss\n\nP.S: I can see a lot of reels getting made saying that brown rice is unhealthy and should not be eaten because of its high content of arsenic. \n\nHowever, the fact is that our ancestors always had brown rice which was unpolished. Nobody is asking people to have rice with the husk. So, let us not believe in every thing that is said in a very technical manner, but also use a little bit of common sense. The best brown rice is the one that is partially polished as you can see in the reel. \n\nIt is easier to cook, tastier and also keeps you full for a longer time. That is why it helps in weight loss as well as blood sugar management.",
