    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Healthy doesn’t mean CALORIE FREE or FAT FREE!\n\nMost of us think that nuts are extremely healthy and must be had in good amounts on a daily basis.\n\nFACT:\n\n👉 Nuts are high on calories & also fat. \n\n👉 A single serving of nuts therefore must not be more than 2 to 3 pieces at a time. \n\nCONCLUSION:\n\n✅ Eating the right nuts in the “right quantity” can help to curb sugar cravings & provide you with energy & fat-soluble vitamins. \n\nEXAMPLE: \n\nWalnuts are in high omega fats, cashews in magnesium & so on. \n\nSo, consuming 2 to 3 each day is enough for fueling your body with nutrients essential for a healthy body and mind.",
