    "descriptionPlain": "All of us feel very good after buying a “low calorie” version or a “fortified with” label... is it really worth your time and money?\n\nMy take:\nNo! there are just 2 types in reality- healthy and unhealthy.\n\nThere is no point eating a healthier version of an item that is unhealthy - let’s say ‘baked chips’ or ‘fat-free chakli’.\n\nThese are still high in fat and sodium as well. \n\nWhat to do then - \n1. Whenever you crave, just have the actual chips, bread or chakli. It will ensure you don’t overdo the portion on the pretext of it being healthy and satisfying your craving.\n\n2. Have it rarely or occasionally - use it as a reward for yourself �",
