    "id": "357",
    "title": "Should we add ghee to our diets?",
    "category": "General",
    "subType": "Gyan",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": null,
    "descriptionPlain": "Our favourite desi superfood! \n\nLoved by dadis, nanis & mummies :) So ghee or no ghee ??? Should we ? Should we not? How much should we?\n\nMy take :\n\n#Ghee is a saturated fat just like what is found in butter, cheese, milk or other milk products. We have Modern day saturated fats we find in biscuits, cakes, puffs, mayonnaise too. Most of them are in INVISIBLE form.\n\nWhen our older generation spoke of the benefits of ghee, India was a nation that ate roti, subji, dal, and rice predominantly and not Pav bhaji, pizza, nachos or other dishes that came with their amounts of saturated fats.\n\nWe ate delicacies only at festivals, laddoos only happened in winter and chikkis in January.. now it’s all available throughout the year.\n\nSo it is our choice now, whether to get our saturated fat from ghee by eating shuddh desi food seasonally or create a balance by including modern foods in smart amounts.\n\nWe can’t have ghee roti or desi food for lunch AND pizza (cheese)or Paav bhaji (butter) for dinner.\n\nOlder generations worked hard, and had to walk miles to get water or wash clothes..we must realize we are 3% as active as them.\n\nSo let’s not be under the impression of ghee is good and so is cheese and butter, it’s always a smart choice we need to make",
