    "descriptionPlain": "Before you freak out here is the latest report sent out by the World Health Organization (WHO) about this peculiar ingredient:\n\n 👉🏻 Aspartame is one of the world’s most popular artificial sweeteners used in various diet cold drinks, desserts, cereals, chewing gum, ice cream, yoghurts and many more food products.\n\n👉🏻 This sweetener became popular as it does not raise blood sugar levels, unlike sugar. Thus, it’s used in a lot of zero-sugar or sugar-free foods & beverages \n\n👉🏻 The WHO has labelled this sweetener as a possible carcinogen (cancer-causing agent)\n\nWould this stop you from drinking Diet Coke or not?",
