    "descriptionPlain": "If you are Constipated, add this High Fiber-Fruit Chia Pudding to your Breakfast thrice a week!\n\n??Dietary fiber is an important nutrient that aids in digestion. Soaked chia seeds contains 40% fiber which brings them to the top of the list of fiber-rich food!\n\n??The gel formed is due to mucilage and digestible fiber and helps in stool movements!\n\n??It not only helps to relieve constipation but also in regulating body weight, blood sugar level & health of the colon!\n\nBut don’t forget to drink water throughout the whole day for this recipe to work well or it can cause you issues like bloating, diarrhea & stomach ache\n\nHere’s how you can make it ?\nRecipe:\n\n*Milk of your choice- 100 ml\n*Soaked Chia seeds - 1.5 tsp\n*Mixed Fruits (avoid mango if diabetic) - 1 katori\n*Almonds/Walnuts- 2-3 pieces\n*Cinnamon Powder - a pinch\n\nStep 1:\nMix milk and soaked Chia seeds in a bowl\n\nStep 2 :\nStore it in the refrigerator for an hour\n\nStep 3 :\nTop it with cinnamon, fresh fruit & nuts of your choice!",
