    "descriptionPlain": "Click here to know.\nPotatoes are fat free!\nMost of us blame the potato as a reason for weight gain, diabetes & other issues.\n• The real culprits are recipes made out of it like chips, fries, aloo fry subjis and not the humble potato.\n* Most of us consider it as a ‘vegetable’ but it is a carbohydrate source (like roti/ rice) hence has to be treated like one.\n\n* Aloo subji with rice / roti or Pav bhaji is a double carb serving in one meal. Avoid if you are trying to lose weight or have uncontrolled blood sugars.\n\n* Aloo peanut upvas subji ( less oil, boiled potatoes) with a bowl of fruits and katori of curd is a perfect meal. You don’t need a sabudana khichadi here.\n\n* A bowl of Mexican soup with a serving of potato, grilled chicken with a serving of boiled potatoes etc are a healthier way to have the potato.",
