    "id": "283",
    "title": "Know about your body type.",
    "category": "Cardiac",
    "subType": "Tips",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dg4wzx8c8/image/upload/v1754556495/social_post/images/xcrkmcegizzu7mfbinuo.jpg",
    "descriptionPlain": "Click here.\nI want to be like Kareena / Katrina / Anushka!\nWe have a few clients who are always looking to reach a particular WEIGHT!\nMy take:\nBodyweight comprises bones, muscles, water, and fat. While many of us have heavier and broader bones, few of us have higher muscle and the remaining have high fat.\nOur appearance differs on these parameters and not the number on the scale.\nRather than the weight only as a parameter, it is healthy and practical for your dietitian to also understand your NATIONALITY, ETHNIC BACKGROUND & BODY TYPE and plan diets accordingly!\nThis will ensure you look at YOUR best & Healthy.\n3 BODY TYPES:\nEctomorphs are thin individuals characterized by smaller bone structures and thinner limbs. This profile is linked to a fast metabolic rate and high carbohydrate tolerance.\nMesomorphs have a medium-sized bone structure and athletic body, and if they’re active, they usually have a considerable amount of lean mass. This profile leads to a predisposition for muscle gain and the maintenance of lower body fat.\nEndomorphs have a larger bone structure with higher amounts of total body mass and fat mass. They tend to be naturally less active.\nBalance Nutrition not only understands the weight but also body type and plans your charts depending on the same.",
