    "id": "289",
    "title": "Fasting or Feasting?",
    "category": "Gut Health",
    "subType": "Tips",
    "mediaType": "static",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "videoType": null,
    "youtubeId": null,
    "imageUrl": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dg4wzx8c8/image/upload/v1754556661/social_post/images/crgq8qqwgetsxzqxwimw.jpg",
    "descriptionPlain": "Choose better.\nARE YOU FASTING/FEASTING? :)\nSABUDANA\nIt is very high in calories and all are empty calories, meaning they contain no other nutrient other than pure simple carbs. So best avoided during fasts .\nKUTTU KA ATTA\nBuckwheat's (kuttu) is rich in antioxidants. Buckwheat helps in cholesterol-lowering. It is a rich source of manganese, copper and magnesium.\nHEALTHY RECIPES- chilla, roti/ paratha and also khichdi.\nAMARANTH FLOUR/ RAJGIRE KA ATTA\nAmaranth or rajgira means “immortal” or “everlasting” in Greek because it contains more than three times the average amount of calcium and is also high in iron.\nRajgira also reduces one’s risk of osteoporosis, because it has twice the amount of calcium as milk.\nHEALTHY RECIPES - thepla, rajgira porridge are some fast recipe options made from this wonder grain.\nMAKAHNE/ FOX NUTS\nIt is rich in proteins, antioxidants , magnesium and has anti ageing properties. It relieves aches and pains and fatigue.\nMakhana can be popped and used as a filler, also can be used in kheer .\nWATERCHESNUT FLOUR/ SINGHARE KA ATTA\nIt is rich in minerals is low in sodium. It is also a rich source of fibre . It has a good effect on hair and skin.\nSinghare ka atta can be used to make dosa, porridge, and thalipeeth.\nBARNYARD MILLET FLOUR/ SAMA KE CHAVAL\nMillets are rich in B vitamins, calcium, iron, potassium, magnesium, zinc, also gluten-free and has low-GI (Glycemic index) thus millets are suitable for people allergies/intolerance of wheat. Also for diabetic, weight loss millets are excellent.\nSama ke chawal can be used to make kheer , upma , pulav and dosas.\nSWEET POTATO\nSweet potatoes pack a powerful nutritional punch. They have got over 400% of your daily needs for vitamin A in one medium spud. Sweet potatoes are a great source of beta-carotene, a powerful antioxidant known to give orange vegetables and fruits their vibrant color, which is converted to vitamin A in the body\nSweet potato can be just boiled and eaten as a snack and also can be used to make tikkis.",
    "tags": [
      "Acidity",
      "calories",
      "cholesterol",
      "buckwheat",
      "copper",
      "manganese",
      "magnesium"
    ],
    "instagramUrl": null,
