    "descriptionPlain": "Maybe we know the reason -->\nMost of us wonder why are we bloated or our blood pressure is still high when we have almost stopped using the salt shaker?\nThe culprits are biscuits, ketchup, pickles, papads and a lot more such foods...\nTo reduce your daily sodium intake, eat low sodium foods like fresh fruits and vegetables, oats, yogurt, etc.\nEat more home-cooked meals to reduce sodium levels, as packaged foods and meals served in restaurants are typically much higher in sodium.\nBe wise and always read the labels to see the sodium content!",
