    "imageUrl": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dg4wzx8c8/image/upload/v1763621604/social_post/images/vtyqtgwfcyera5mywwse.png",
    "descriptionPlain": "Know this before you consume nuts.\n\r\nNuts are healthy, filling & contain very good amount of essential plant fat as well as fiber.\nHowever, they are also high in calories & lead to weight gain. (high portions)\nHere are things to be careful of before adding nuts to your diet:\n1. Portion sizes & Frequency:\nYou may think that eating five almonds in a day is very healthy. But if you compare and add up your monthly consumption of almonds, it is 150, almonds being consumed in a matter of 30 days!\n2. Having roasted, salted or flavoured nuts. This increases your calories exponentially. So be very careful and have only unsalted nuts.\n3. Having nut butters with added sugars, flavours and salts.\nThese again come in the weight gain category!\n4. Adding nuts to high-calorie dishes like shakes, biryanis and desserts.",
