    "descriptionPlain": "Follow this for a healthy lifestyle\n\r\nThrow away these things from your kitchen:\n\nKetchup: Ketchup is one condiment that seems to enter our food unknowingly. I have seen children having all their meals only with ketchup. It is high in sugar, preservatives and should not be consumed. Healthier alternatives include chutneys made from tamarind and dates. You will get the same taste.\n\nSugar-Free Sweeteners: Sugar-free Indian sweets are made using dates and anjeer (figs), both of which are very high in natural sugars as well as calories. Artificial sweeteners when added to a dessert do not make it healthy or calorie free. If you crave a dessert, you must try the two bite rule.\n\n\"Healthy\" Biscuits: Even the so called 'healthy' biscuits that claim to be sugar-free or low-fat, often have surprising amount of additives, hidden sugars and empty calories.\n\nSoup Diets: Not just soup diet but any other diets that claim to give good results very quickly should be off your list. Weight loss happens only when you practically make changes to your diet.",
