    "imageUrl": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dg4wzx8c8/image/upload/v1754559461/social_post/images/dgniiywvzpnqix7lmy08.jpg",
    "descriptionPlain": "Whic is better for you?\nCardio or weights? Which is the best exercise after all !\n\nAny form of cardio like cycling, walking, jogging or swimming is called aerobic.\nThis means that it requires a lot of breathing and works directly by increasing the heart rate and basic metabolic them.\nThis is best for someone who has a high fat percentage and is overweight.\nIt is also a very good exercise for someone who struggles to climb 2 floors without panting, someone who wants to participate in a marathon or any other aerobic/cardio activity.\nIt is also a good alternative for senior citizens who have weak joints & weak stamina.\nIf you have to increase your muscle mass, bone mass and are not waiting too much, then waits becomes a good exercise.\nLifting weights is an anaerobic activity, meaning it does not require constant breathing and is focusing on developing muscles.",
    "tags": [
      "Gain Weight"
    ],
